Conclusion following previous exercise

Using this analysis we cannot decide whether the stationary point at \(x=0\) is a local maximum, minimum or a point of inflection. However, just to the left of \(x=0\) the value of \(\dfrac{\mathrm{d}f}{\mathrm{d}x}\) (which equals \(x^2(4x-1)\)) is negative whilst just to the right of \(x=0\) the value of \(\dfrac{\mathrm{d}f}{\mathrm{d}x}\) is negative again. Hence the stationary point at \(x=0\) is a point of inflection. This is confirmed by sketching the curve below.
